        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-02 10:22:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\nLet's discuss this in Scrum today.",
        "patchset_number": 11
      },
      {
        "id": "c6245be42ee981c6c0e7554bc4327e43f03280e0",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-02 10:25:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\n> I am ok with this. It's just that Liam is also planning to bring 2\n > sets of models - authorative (with basic pojo structure) &\n > persistence (with JPA implementation). Also the mapping between\n > these 2 sets. In that case, we will not need to maintain 1 more set\n > in policy-models-pap and the corresponding Mapper which this review\n > is bringing in.\n > I am ok if we want to bring it in now and delete later.\n\nThe \"authorative\" model for this will be models-pdp (or will replace models-pdp).  However, the external REST API will not use the \"authorative\" model; it will uses models-pap, thus a mapper will still be needed.  Or would you prefer we eliminate the mapper and add toAuthorative/fromAuthorative methods to the classes in models-pap?",
        "patchset_number": 11
      },
      {
        "id": "e659681ddc4f6e3292012f04a465d8558b88dfde",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3239,
          "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
          "username": "ramverma"
