        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-02 10:46:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\n> > I am ok with this. It's just that Liam is also planning to bring\n > 2\n > > sets of models - authorative (with basic pojo structure) &\n > > persistence (with JPA implementation). Also the mapping between\n > > these 2 sets. In that case, we will not need to maintain 1 more\n > set\n > > in policy-models-pap and the corresponding Mapper which this\n > review\n > > is bringing in.\n > > I am ok if we want to bring it in now and delete later.\n > \n > The \"authorative\" model for this will be models-pdp (or will\n > replace models-pdp).  However, the external REST API will not use\n > the \"authorative\" model; it will uses models-pap, thus a mapper\n > will still be needed.  Or would you prefer we eliminate the mapper\n > and add toAuthorative/fromAuthorative methods to the classes in\n > models-pap?\n\nWhy can't we use \"authorative\" models from models-pdp directly in REST if they are exactly same?",
        "patchset_number": 11
      },
