        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-02 11:24:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\n> > Why can't we use \"authorative\" models from models-pdp directly in\n > > REST if they are exactly same?\n > \n > That would be fine with me, but would require a couple of changes\n > to the REST API: 1) change PdpInstanceDetails to Pdp  2) change\n > Policy to ToscaPolicy\n\nI think it should be Policy in the \"authorative\" models and not ToscaPolicy. Let's check with Liam in Scrum today.",
